The question that I would like to raise is  - Would Goa have done much better with more political stability ? I expect all stakeholders and in particular, the legislators assembled here to deeply reflect on this issue: @MVenkaiahNaidu @VPSecretariat at Goa Assembly https://t.co/uvt8Y3D4d4

Goa has had as many as 30 governments during the last 57 years. This is quite a huge number by any reckoning.  11 of these 30 governments had tenure of less than one year each ranging from 6 days   to 334 days: @MVenkaiahNaidu @VPSecretariat at Goa Assembly https://t.co/F3tgmbMxrA
All these require highly skilled manpower which the State needs to build in quick time: @MVenkaiahNaidu @VPSecretariat at Goa Assembly https://t.co/TEjFnhtvXL

Goa has now to look for diversification of its growth engines by seizing the opportunities being offered by the 'new economy' in the domains of Information Technology, Bio-Technology, start-up entrepreneurship etc.

While it is a challenge to reach the pinnacle as Goa did, it is an equally formidable challenge to hold on to that position by avoiding any slippages: @MVenkaiahNaidu @VPSecretariat at Goa Assembly https://t.co/WLYrTJx3in

I compliment all the successive governments and the people of Goa for their remarkable journey since liberation and for being the most developed state in the country: @MVenkaiahNaidu @VPSecretariat at Goa Assembly https://t.co/AbYM1P3fpn

As Goa entered the 60th year of liberation, I take this opportunity to pay my homage to the leaders of the long drawn liberation movement & the people who had suffered worst in their quest for freedom and for being the masters of their own destiny: @MVenkaiahNaidu @VPSecretariat https://t.co/lQ3zTv4Acv

Government and the people of Goa did remarkably well in handling the pandemic and in the process emerged as an example for others: @MVenkaiahNaidu @VPSecretariat at Goa Assembly https://t.co/dTmq5C8KHZ

India was expected to be severely impacted in terms of case load & mortalities and the consequences.
